 pan over a medium-high heat and cook bread for 1 minute on each side, then set aside to keep warm.","Returning to curry, set Varoma aside then add tomatoes and coconut milk to mixing bowl. Return Varoma to position then cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Remove Varoma and set aside. Add spinach to mixing bowl and stir through with spatula. Serve curry with chicken and sugar snap peas on top, accompanied by the flatbreads."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Preparation Before Demo","content":["320 - 350 g aubergines, diced (1 cm) (1-2 aubergines)","400 g chicken breasts, halved horizontally then sliced (0.5 cm)","200 g sugar snap peas              (optional)"]},{"title":"Quick Flatbreads","content":["350 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","250 g plain yoghurt","1 tsp baking powder","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp granulated sugar"]},{"title":"Frozen Fruit Sorbet","content":["50 g sugar, adjust to taste","500 g frozen fruit, (e.g. banana and strawberry mix)","2 tsp lemon juice              (optional)","1 egg white, from medium or large egg (optional)"]},{"title":"Aubergine, Spinach and Lentil Curry","content":["120 g onions, quartered (1 onion)","2 garlic cloves","20 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 fresh green chilli, halved (with seeds)","15 g olive oil","150 g red split lentils, rinsed","15 g tomato purée","300 g water","3 tsp garam masala","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 vegetable stock cube (for 0.5 l)","350 g cherry tomatoes, halved","400 g coconut milk","150 g fresh spinach leaves"]}],"id":"r214853","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-AzYEwv6Fzfg\/XZQF_L6ye4I\/AAAAAAAAb44\/yfEnVfG4yrsHuD5fIFaswD3E6hgtMMsuACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Fx944PBeuFwbf8Fy.png","title":"Chicken, Aubergine, Spinach and Lentil Curry, Quick Flatbreads, Frozen Fruit Sorbet","publishedAt":"2017-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"33.6 g","fat":"18.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"83.7 g","calories":"2747 kJ \/ 657 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rolling pin, serving bowls, large bowl, griddle pan, freezer-proof container, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Fruits should be frozen in individual pieces or small clusters. Cut fruit in pieces, spread out on a tray, freeze, then use frozen fruit in recipe or transfer to a freezer bag for later use.","A frying pan can be used if a griddle pan is not available.","For a vegetarian version, omit the chicken."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","1 portion"]}